{"brand":"Adox","name":"CHS 100 II","iso":100,"filmType":"bw-negative","process":"bw","formats":["135","120","4x5"],"base":"polyester","spectralSensitivity":"orthopanchromatic","grainRms":null,"datasheetUrl":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/44450_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","notes":"Classic single-layer emulsion made from two emulsions; sensitization optimized for greyscale separation and large exposure latitude. Coated on clear archival PET (100 micron for 135 and 120; 175 micron for sheetfilm). Can be reversal processed. AHU plus backside AH/NC layer in 135 and 120; backside AH/NC layer only in sheetfilm. Made in Germany. Datasheet hosted by Fotoimpex, authored by ADOX Fotowerke GmbH.","image":"https://www.adox.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/CHS100IIFilm-01-01.png","productUrl":"https://www.adox.de/adox-filme-2/adox-chs-100-typ-ii/","documents":[{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/44450_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox CHS 100 II technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"}],"specSources":[{"document":{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/44450_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox CHS 100 II technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"fields":["brand","name","iso","filmType","process","formats","base","spectralSensitivity","variants"],"method":"manual-transcription"}],"variants":[{"format":"135","base":"polyester","baseThickness":{"value":100,"unit":"um"}},{"format":"120","base":"polyester","baseThickness":{"value":100,"unit":"um"}},{"format":"4x5","base":"polyester","baseThickness":{"value":175,"unit":"um"}}]}
{"brand":"Adox","name":"CMS 20 II","iso":20,"filmType":"bw-negative","process":"bw","formats":["135"],"base":"polyester","spectralSensitivity":"orthopanchromatic","grainRms":null,"datasheetUrl":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/62175_4_PDF-Datenblatt.pdf","notes":"Ultra-high-resolution monodisperse emulsion resolving up to 800 lp/mm. Rated 20 ASA in dedicated ADOTECH developer (pictorial); up to 80 ASA for high contrast; 3-6 ASA in non-dedicated low-contrast developers. AHU anti-halation layer between emulsion and base; totally transparent base. Reciprocity: +1/2 stop at 1s and at 1/1000s. Datasheet hosted by Fotoimpex, authored by ADOX Fotowerke GmbH.","image":"https://www.adox.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/CMS20II-FIlm-01.png","productUrl":"https://www.adox.de/adox-filme-2/adox-cms-20/","documents":[{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/62175_4_PDF-Datenblatt.pdf","title":"Adox CMS 20 II technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"}],"specSources":[{"document":{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/62175_4_PDF-Datenblatt.pdf","title":"Adox CMS 20 II technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"fields":["brand","name","iso","filmType","process","formats","base","spectralSensitivity","reciprocityPoints"],"method":"manual-transcription"}],"reciprocityPoints":[{"meteredSeconds":1,"correctionStops":{"value":5,"unit":"stop","scale":10}}]}
{"brand":"Adox","name":"HR-50","iso":50,"filmType":"bw-negative","process":"bw","formats":["135","120","4x5"],"base":"polyester","spectralSensitivity":"superpanchromatic","grainRms":null,"datasheetUrl":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/63360_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","notes":"High-resolution film based on a technical emulsion; speed boosted to 50 ASA (ISO 50/17°) via ADOX SPEED BOOST technology, gamma reduced for pictorial use. Resolution up to 280 lp/mm at 1000:1 image contrast. Base 0.1mm PET; combined AHU/NC anti-halation. Usable as an infrared film and responds strongly to filtration. Datasheet hosted by Fotoimpex, authored by ADOX Fotowerke GmbH.","image":"https://www.adox.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/HR-50Film-01.png","productUrl":"https://www.adox.de/adox-hr-50/","documents":[{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/63360_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox HR-50 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"}],"specSources":[{"document":{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/63360_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox HR-50 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"fields":["brand","name","iso","filmType","process","formats","base","spectralSensitivity","resolvingPowerTests"],"method":"manual-transcription"}],"resolvingPowerTests":[{"linesPerMm":280,"contrastRatio":"1000:1"}]}
{"brand":"Adox","name":"Scala 160","iso":160,"filmType":"bw-slide","process":"reversal-bw","formats":["135"],"base":"triacetate","spectralSensitivity":"panchromatic","grainRms":null,"datasheetUrl":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/59440_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","notes":"Black and white reversal (slide) film designed specifically for reversal processing at 160 ASA; dedicated ADOX SCALA reversal kit available. Coated on 120 micron clear triacetate with increased silver content, yielding DMAX of 3.6 or higher. Anti-halation layer between emulsion and base. Not DX coded. When shot as a negative, expose at 80-100 ASA. Reciprocity: +1/2 from 1s, +1 from 10s, +2 from 100s. No standalone PDF; specifications published on official ADOX product page.","image":"https://www.adox.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/SCALA160-01.png","productUrl":"https://www.adox.de/adox-scala-160/","documents":[{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/59440_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox Scala 160 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"}],"specSources":[{"document":{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/59440_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox Scala 160 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"fields":["brand","name","iso","filmType","process","formats","base","spectralSensitivity","variants","reciprocityPoints"],"method":"manual-transcription"}],"variants":[{"format":"135","base":"triacetate","baseThickness":{"value":120,"unit":"um"}}],"reciprocityPoints":[{"meteredSeconds":1,"correctionStops":{"value":5,"unit":"stop","scale":10}},{"meteredSeconds":10,"correctionStops":{"value":1,"unit":"stop"}},{"meteredSeconds":100,"correctionStops":{"value":2,"unit":"stop"}}]}
{"brand":"Adox","name":"Scala 50","iso":50,"filmType":"bw-slide","process":"reversal-bw","formats":["135","120","4x5"],"base":"polyester","spectralSensitivity":"superpanchromatic","grainRms":null,"datasheetUrl":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/64170_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","notes":"High-resolution B&W slide film based on a technical emulsion; speed boosted to 50 ASA (ISO 50/17°) with gamma reduced for pictorial use. Resolution up to 280 lp/mm at 1000:1 image contrast. Base 0.1mm PET; combined AHU/NC anti-halation. Processed as a slide in the dedicated ADOX SCALA reversal kit; can also be processed as a negative using HR-50 times. Usable as an infrared film. No standalone PDF; specifications published on official ADOX product page.","image":"https://www.adox.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Scala50Film-01.png","productUrl":"https://www.adox.de/scala-50/","documents":[{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/64170_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox Scala 50 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"}],"specSources":[{"document":{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/64170_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox Scala 50 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"fields":["brand","name","iso","filmType","process","formats","base","spectralSensitivity","resolvingPowerTests"],"method":"manual-transcription"}],"resolvingPowerTests":[{"linesPerMm":280,"contrastRatio":"1000:1"}]}
{"brand":"Adox","name":"Silvermax 100","iso":100,"filmType":"bw-negative","process":"bw","formats":["135"],"base":"triacetate","spectralSensitivity":"panchromatic","grainRms":null,"datasheetUrl":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/42205_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","notes":"Currently discontinued (ADOX recommends CHS 100 II / Scala 50 as alternatives). APX 100 recipe with finer grain, slightly lower speed and ~30% higher silver content. Achieves up to 14 stops copy range in dedicated Silvermax developer. Coated on 120 micron clear triacetate; anti-halation layer between emulsion and base; can optionally be reversal-processed to a B&W slide (ADOX Scala). Not DX coded. Reciprocity: +1/2 from 1s, +1 from 10s, +2 from 100s. Made in Germany. Datasheet hosted by Fotoimpex, authored by ADOX Fotowerke GmbH.","image":"https://www.adox.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/SILVERMAX-Kopie.png","productUrl":"https://www.adox.de/adox-filme-2/adox-silvermax/","documents":[{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/42205_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox Silvermax 100 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"}],"specSources":[{"document":{"kind":"technical-data","asset":{"url":"https://www.fotoimpex.de/shop/images/products/media/42205_5_PDF-Datasheet.pdf","title":"Adox Silvermax 100 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"fields":["brand","name","iso","filmType","process","formats","base","spectralSensitivity","variants","reciprocityPoints"],"method":"manual-transcription"}],"variants":[{"format":"135","base":"triacetate","baseThickness":{"value":120,"unit":"um"}}],"reciprocityPoints":[{"meteredSeconds":1,"correctionStops":{"value":5,"unit":"stop","scale":10}},{"meteredSeconds":10,"correctionStops":{"value":1,"unit":"stop"}},{"meteredSeconds":100,"correctionStops":{"value":2,"unit":"stop"}}]}
{"brand":"Adox","name":"PAN-X Reverso Super 8","iso":100,"filmType":"bw-slide","process":"reversal-bw","formats":["super8"],"base":"triacetate","spectralSensitivity":"panchromatic","grainRms":null,"datasheetUrl":"https://www.adox.de/films/pan-x-reverso-super8-en/","notes":"True B&W Super 8 reversal film, projectable right after development; positioned as a replacement for the discontinued Kodak Plus-X. Currently unavailable. Silver-rich emulsion with full shadow detail at 100 ASA and DMAX above 3.0; anti-halation layer between base and emulsion; clear triacetate base. 15 meters (~3 min 20 s). Standard developing in Kodak D-94A process; expose at 64 or 100 ASA (best results at 64 ASA); cartridge notched 100 ASA Tungsten. No standalone PDF; specifications published on official ADOX product page.","image":"https://www.adox.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/PAN-X1.png","productUrl":"https://www.adox.de/adox-filme-2/adox-pan-x-reverso-super8-2/","documents":[{"kind":"product-page","asset":{"url":"https://www.adox.de/films/pan-x-reverso-super8-en/","title":"Adox PAN-X Reverso Super 8 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"}],"specSources":[{"document":{"kind":"product-page","asset":{"url":"https://www.adox.de/films/pan-x-reverso-super8-en/","title":"Adox PAN-X Reverso Super 8 technical data","source":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"publisher":"ADOX Fotowerke GmbH"},"fields":["brand","name","iso","filmType","process","formats","base","spectralSensitivity"],"method":"manual-transcription"}]}
